OL,3,CWho are the senior Labour figures
OL,4,Cvying to replace Sir Keir Starmer?
OL,6,FMany within his party saw these
OL,7,Fpledges as disappointing but they
OL,8,Fincluded moves to nationalise British
OL,9,FSteel, forge much closer ties with
OL,10,FEurope, and to ensure young people
OL,11,Fcurrently out of work have a guarantee
OL,12,Fof a job, training or education.
OL,14,FSir Keir has warned against the Labour
OL,15,FParty tacking to either the left or
OL,16,Fthe right in the wake of the election
OL,17,Fdefeats and has cast the current
OL,18,Fpolitical moment as a "battle for the
OL,19,Fsoul" of the UK.
OL,26,@zD@WOU{D@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
